  A 17-YEAR old student of Federal Government College, Rubochi, in the Federal Capital Territory (FCT), Abuja was abducted in the early hours of Tuesday, The Nation gathered. It was learnt the male student, identified as Gift Abiikor, was abducted while he was sleeping around 1am in the residence of one Ahmed Adamu, who reported the incident to the police. A statement by the Federal Capital Territory police command indicated that the Commissioner of Police, CP Bala Ciroma has ordered an investigation into the incident. The statement by the police spokesman, DSP Anjuguri Manzah, read, “According to Ahmed Adamu who reported the incident to the police, some armed men stormed his house and abducted one Gift Abiikor who was sleeping on the same bed with Ahmed Adamu’s children.”   